setVehiclePosition.Hover:
[Global argument][Global effect]

### Description:
Moves the object to a given position (same as createVehicle placement algorithm). Uses either the position that's defined by the  param, or one of the marker positions from the markers array. The object is placed inside a circle with  as its center and  as its radius. The type of placement could also be controlled with . 

If position is in water and vehicle can float, it is placed on water surface, otherwise it is placed on the ground, even if ground is under water. If roof surfaces support walking, units will be placed on roofs if such position is given.


### Syntax:
object setVehiclePosition [position, markers, placement, special]

### Parameters:
object: Object
[position, markers, placement, special]: Array
position: PositionATL (PositionAGL if boat or amphibious), Position2D, or Object - Desired placement position. If object is given, object position is used for . Normally only  and  are considered, unless "CAN_COLLIDE" is used for special placement.
markers: Array of Strings - If the markers array contains one or more marker names, the position is chosen randomly and could be one of the marker positions or just the supplied main position. If marker had z coordinate set with setMarkerPos, the vehicle will be placed on the nearest surface below this z coordinate
placement: Number - The vehicle is randomly placed inside a circle with given position as center and placement as its radius
special (Optional): String - Could be one of the following: 

If  is "" or not specified, default "NONE" is used.

### Return Value:
Boolean - true on success, false on failure


### Example 1:

```sqf
player setVehiclePosition [[1000,2000], ["Pos1","Pos2","Pos3"], 0, "CAN_COLLIDE"];
```
 Will place the player at either [1000,2000], or one of the three markers positions.

### Example 2:

```sqf
